<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.realpoor.com">Tarew Marr</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorbadintriton>Thorbadin Triton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/02 10:52:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2591.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Some truth in there.</span><hr size=1> First, hard cap mean that the number itself cannot go over the cap.  The stats cap is a hard cap, weapons skills and now it seem that the innate atk is caped at 250, etc.  <br>
<br>
A soft cap is still a cap, but the numbers can still visibly  increase.  <br>
<br>
Everyone that did a serious parse in velious/luclin basically said that past a point &quot;the soft cap&quot; the mob was doing the same damage whatever the ac of the tank was.  That's the cap, and it was identified to be at 1250 or so.  There is no diminushing returns like it work below the cap, since a diminushing returns implies that there is no cap.<br>
<br>
That cap probably still exist in velious/luclin in order to not trivialize the content even more.<br>
<br>
The &quot;rumor&quot; is that there is no AC cap anymore in POP, at least not in any range of attainable ac.<br>
<br>
Now, there was always a diminushing returns on ac vs the same mob (below the cap) past a certain point, but that logic can still be applied to POP without having the need to put in a cap anywhere.<br>
<br>
Just that as your ac progress you will take less damage from a mob as the mob difficulty increase their atk increase and you need more ac to compensate.  <br>
<br>
Thorbadin<br>
Triton <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khumak>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/02 11:00:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2591.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Some truth in there.</span><hr size=1> Maybe I'm crazy but it seems to me like the ATK rating of many of the mobs in PoP is actually LOWER than in Luclin.  Sure, the max hit is high but how many times do you actually get hit for max?  I find a fairly good distribution of hits from PoP mobs all the way from Min hit to Max hit.  My theory is that they did this on purpose to make mitigation count in PoP.  Anyway maybe I'm wrong but that's my perception.<br>
<br>
Case in point, I tanked the boss mob in the hedge in PoN.  His max hit was 1184 but his most common hit was 181.  This is with an AC of about 1330-1350. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Overlord<br>
Mith Marr<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=remfdatroll@thesteelwarrior>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/02 11:50:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2591.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Some truth in there.</span><hr size=1> Heyas-<br>
<br>
Healers in PoV (killing golems, guards, fiends and such) noted that I was taking significantly more damage at AC1350ish than I had been at ~1480... I'd swapped my vindi BP out for a fungi to help conserve mana, but the result was the exact opposite.  Dunno if it was a change in AGI, AC, or both tho, and it wasn't more than annecdotal evidence...<br>
<br>
Should be possible to &quot;map out&quot; the higher end DPS vs. AC numbers now tho, many more high level mobs to test with, and higher AC (both mitigation and avoidance) available.  See if the old rule of thumb about AC over 1300 being diminishing returns still applies... I'm starting to think it doesn't.<br>
<br>
I've also switched almost entirely to 2h weapons for tanking in PoP, even with TM... ripostes by mobs that hit as hard as the yard trash there does sucks up healer mana way too fast during exp grinds, and 2h taunt seems MUCH better than it once was...<br>
